dublin_core.dcvalue: Have a mobile tool that creates more data than you actually use What if it were possible to take advantage of all of that automatically generated data to discover new insights about your mHealth intervention all with a few simple Excel tricks In this workshop you will gain hands on experience applying simple data analysis techniques that will help you use data coming out of your mHealth intervention Our practical program friendly approach to data analysis will provide program implementers with a set of starter tools to identify key descriptive characteristics of data without using advanced statistical programs No prior data analysis experience necessary Presented by Lindsey Tyler Leslie Program Officer Johns Hopkins Center for Communication Programs
Digging into Data: Quick and Dirty Analysis Tips for mHealth Program Implementers
